{
  "texts": [
    "Allowing users to provide preferences may help address the affordance challenge of explainable recommendation systems.",
    "Fourthly, considering all the perspectives, the proposed synthesized diagram for explainable AI-based recommendation system development can be used along with the concept of design science research to develop a user-centric explainable recommendation system development (Hevner et al., 2004; Peffers et al., 2007).",
    "Though the proposed framework only addresses the issue of user interface development, it can be extended and adopted to develop the whole system, making it an essential contribution for practitioners.",
    "Finally, our work can be a suitable example that addresses the policy guidelines of HLEG, the AI Act, and GDPR to some extent (Durovic & Corno, 2025).",
    "The empirical findings in our work reveal that explainability can help establish transparency and informed decision-making and detect bias by the end users."
  ]
}